file.name: active_directory.yaml
file.content:
components:
  schemas:
    tmp0:
      properties:
        successful: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp1:
      properties:
        successful: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp10:
      properties:
        accountExpires: {type: string}
        badPasswordTime: {type: string}
        badPwdCount: {type: string}
        cn: {type: string}
        codePage: {type: string}
        countryCode: {type: string}
        dSCorePropagationData: {type: string}
        distinguishedName: {type: string}
        instanceType: {type: string}
        isCriticalSystemObject: {type: string}
        lastLogoff: {type: string}
        lastLogon: {type: string}
        localPolicyFlags: {type: string}
        location: {type: string}
        logonCount: {type: string}
        name: {type: string}
        objectCategory: {type: string}
        objectClass: {type: string}
        objectGUID: {type: string}
        objectSid: {type: string}
        primaryGroupID: {type: string}
        pwdLastSet: {type: string}
        raw_json: {type: string}
        sAMAccountName: {type: string}
        sAMAccountType: {type: string}
        uSNChanged: {type: string}
        uSNCreated: {type: string}
        userAccountControl: {type: string}
        whenChanged: {type: string}
        whenCreated: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp11:
      properties:
        accountExpires: {type: string}
        badPasswordTime: {type: string}
        badPwdCount: {type: string}
        cn: {type: string}
        codePage: {type: string}
        countryCode: {type: string}
        dSCorePropagationData: {type: string}
        department: {type: string}
        description: {type: string}
        displayName: {type: string}
        distinguishedName: {type: string}
        givenName: {type: string}
        instanceType: {type: string}
        lastLogoff: {type: string}
        lastLogon: {type: string}
        logonCount: {type: string}
        mail: {type: string}
        manager: {type: string}
        name: {type: string}
        objectCategory: {type: string}
        objectClass: {type: string}
        objectGUID: {type: string}
        objectSid: {type: string}
        physicalDeliveryOfficeName: {type: string}
        primaryGroupID: {type: string}
        pwdLastSet: {type: string}
        raw_json: {type: string}
        sAMAccountName: {type: string}
        sAMAccountType: {type: string}
        sn: {type: string}
        telephoneNumber: {type: string}
        title: {type: string}
        uSNChanged: {type: string}
        uSNCreated: {type: string}
        userAccountControl: {type: string}
        userPrincipalName: {type: string}
        whenChanged: {type: string}
        whenCreated: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp12:
      properties:
        result: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp13:
      properties:
        result: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp14:
      properties:
        is_member: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp2:
      properties:
        success: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp3:
      properties:
        success: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp4:
      properties:
        success: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp5:
      properties:
        success: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp6:
      properties:
        json: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp7:
      properties:
        success: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp8:
      properties:
        result: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp9:
      properties:
        result: {type: string}
      type: object
  securitySchemes: {}
info:
  contact: {email: frikky@shuffler.io, name: '@frikkylikeme', url: 'https://twitter.com/frikkylikeme'}
  description: Automated generation of Microsoft Active Directory
  title: Microsoft Active Directory
  version: 1.0.0
  x-logo: data:image/png;base64,
openapi: 3.0.2
paths:
  tmp0:
    post:
      description: Change a password in active directory
      parameters:
      - description: Full User DN
        example: CN=Helen Powers,CN=Users,DC=example,DC=com
        in: query
        name: User DN
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The new password. Will fail if the password doesn't meet domain
          requirements
        example: mynewp@55word!
        in: query
        name: New Password
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp0'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: AD Change Password
  tmp1:
    post:
      description: Change a password in active directory
      parameters:
      - description: User to test the password of
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: User
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Password to try for the user
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Password
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp1'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: AD Test Password
  tmp10:
    post:
      description: Search for a computer in Active Directory
      parameters:
      - description: The name of the attribute to search on
        example: cn
        in: query
        name: Search Attribute
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The value to match against
        example: DC01
        in: query
        name: Search Value
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp10'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Query System
  tmp11:
    post:
      description: Search for a user in Active Directory
      parameters:
      - description: The name of the attribute to search on
        example: givenName
        in: query
        name: Search Attribute
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The value to match against
        example: Evan
        in: query
        name: Search Value
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp11'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Query User
  tmp12:
    post:
      description: Move a computer to a new container in Active Directory
      parameters:
      - description: The name of the attribute to search on
        example: CN
        in: query
        name: Search Attribute
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The value to match against
        example: DC01
        in: query
        name: Search Value
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: 'DN Prefix + Base DN is the complete DN of the container to which
          the system will be moved: OU=lockdown,CN=Dept_X,DC=example,DC=com'
        example: OU=lockdown,CN=Dept_X
        in: query
        name: Destination Container's DN Prefix
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp12'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Update Container
  tmp13:
    post:
      description: Edit the value of a computer's attribute in Active Directory
      parameters:
      - description: The name of the attribute to search on
        example: CN
        in: query
        name: Search Attribute
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The value to match against
        example: DC01
        in: query
        name: Search Value
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The name of the attribute to update
        example: operatingSystem
        in: query
        name: Update Attribute
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The value to assign to the chosen attribute
        example: Windows Server 2012
        in: query
        name: Update Value
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp13'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Update System
  tmp14:
    post:
      description: Check if a user is a member of a group, including nested groups.
      parameters:
      - description: The name of the attribute to search on
        example: distinguishedName
        in: query
        name: Search Attribute
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The value to match.
        example: CN=Leeroy Jenkins,OU=friends,DC=testdomain,DC=local
        in: query
        name: Search Value
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The distinguished name of the group
        example: CN=test group 2,DC=testdomain,DC=local
        in: query
        name: Group DN
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp14'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: ' User is member of group'
  tmp2:
    post:
      description: Add a user to one or more groups.
      parameters:
      - description: The distinguished name of the user.
        example: CN=MyUser,DC=testdomain,DC=local
        in: query
        name: DN
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: A list of distinguished names for each group that the user will
          be added to.
        example: '[''CN=MyGroup,CN=Users,DC=testdomain,DC=local'']'
        in: query
        name: Groups
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The distinguished name for a single group that the user will
          be added to.
        example: CN=MyGroup,CN=Users,DC=testdomain,DC=local
        in: query
        name: Group
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp2'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: ' Add User to Groups'
  tmp3:
    post:
      description: Require a user to change their password the next time they log
        in.
      parameters:
      - description: The distinguished name of the user.
        example: CN=MyUser,DC=testdomain,DC=local
        in: query
        name: DN
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp3'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: ' Change Password at Next Login'
  tmp4:
    post:
      description: Create a new AD user.
      parameters:
      - description: Distinguished Name
        example: CN=My Name,OU=friends,DC=testdomain,DC=local
        in: query
        name: DN
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: A JSON string containing a mapping of attribute names to attribute
          values.
        example: '{"cn": "Leeroy Jenkins", "displayName": "Leeroy Jenkins", "name":
          "Leeroy Jenkins", "sn": "Jenkins", "givenName": "Leeroy"}'
        in: query
        name: Extra Attributes
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Country
        example: United States
        in: query
        name: Country
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Country Code
        example: '840'
        in: body
        name: Country Code
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: A list of user account control flags.  See README for options
        example: '["NORMAL_ACCOUNT"]'
        in: query
        name: User Account Control Flags
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: User Principal Name
        example: my.name@testdomain.local
        in: query
        name: User Principal Name
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The DN of the user's manager
        example: CN=Chuck Norris,OU=friends,DC=testdomain,DC=local
        in: query
        name: Manager
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Instance Type
        example: '4'
        in: body
        name: Instance Type
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Description
        example: Employee
        in: query
        name: Description
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Title
        example: job title
        in: query
        name: Title
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Street Address
        example: 123 street st
        in: query
        name: Street Address
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: City
        example: Boulder
        in: query
        name: City
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: State
        example: Co
        in: query
        name: State
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Postal Code
        example: '11111'
        in: query
        name: Postal Code
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: ISO standard country code
        example: US
        in: query
        name: ISO standard country code
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Department
        example: department name
        in: query
        name: Department
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: EMail
        example: testemail@tester.com
        in: query
        name: EMail
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: sAMAccountName
        example: leeroy.jenkins
        in: query
        name: sAMaccountName
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Object Category
        example: CN=Person,CN=Schema,CN=Configuration,DC=testdomain,DC=local
        in: query
        name: Object Category
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Company
        example: company
        in: query
        name: Company
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Display Name
        example: My Name
        in: query
        name: Display Name
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Telephone Number
        example: '1111111111'
        in: query
        name: Telephone Number
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Web Page
        example: http://www.sample.com
        in: query
        name: Web Page
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Physical Delivery Office Name
        example: home
        in: query
        name: Physical Delivery Office Name
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Name
        example: My Name
        in: query
        name: Name
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Specifies the code page for the user's language of choice.
        example: '0'
        in: body
        name: Code Page
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: SN
        example: lastname
        in: query
        name: SN
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Given Name
        example: Leeroy
        in: query
        name: Given Name
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Initials
        example: LJ
        in: query
        name: Initials
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp4'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: ' Create User'
  tmp5:
    post:
      description: Add and entry into AD.
      parameters:
      - description: The distinguished name for the object being created.
        example: CN=Nacho Libre,OU=friends,DC=testdomain,DC=local
        in: query
        name: Dn
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: A comma separated list of object classes to add this object to.
        example: top,person,organizationalPerson,user
        in: query
        name: Class Names
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: A JSON string containing a mapping of attribute names to attribute
          values.
        example: '{"attribute1": "value1", "attribute2": "value2"}'
        in: query
        name: Attributes
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp5'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: ' Custom Create'
  tmp6:
    post:
      description: Execute a custom LDAP query.  You can use the available inputs
        to generate the query or create the query yourself and pass it in using the
        Search Filter parameter.
      parameters:
      - description: An LDAP search filter.
        example: (sn=an_sn_value)
        in: query
        name: Search Filter
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Attribute to search on
        example: sn
        in: query
        name: Search Attribute
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Desired value of the search attribute
        example: surfadmin
        in: query
        name: Search Value
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: A comma separated list of attributes to return
        example: sn,creatorsName
        in: query
        name: Return Attributes
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Object Class to search in.
        example: user
        in: query
        name: Object Class
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Object Categoty to search in.
        example: person
        in: query
        name: Object Category
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp6'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: ' Custom Query'
  tmp7:
    post:
      description: Execute a custom LDAP update. You can update a single attribute
        using the inputs provided, or pass in a json mapping of attributes to values
        to update.
      parameters:
      - description: The DN of the object to update
        example: cn=Tom Riddle,ou=Groups,dc=swimlane,dc=us
        in: query
        name: DN
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: JSON with a mapping of attributes to values to update.
        example: '{"attribute1": "value1", "attribute2": "value2"}'
        in: query
        name: Update JSON
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The attribute to update
        example: sn
        in: query
        name: Update Attribute
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The value to update the attribute to.
        example: swimlane
        in: query
        name: Update Value
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp7'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: ' Custom Update'
  tmp8:
    post:
      description: Disable a user in Active Directory
      parameters:
      - description: The name of the attribute to search on
        example: CN
        in: query
        name: Search Attribute
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The value to match against
        example: Evan Contreras
        in: query
        name: Search Value
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp8'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Disable User
  tmp9:
    post:
      description: Enable a user in Active Directory
      parameters:
      - description: The name of the attribute to search on
        example: CN
        in: query
        name: Search Attribute
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The value to match against
        example: Evan Contreras
        in: query
        name: Search Value
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp9'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Enable User
tags:
- {name: Identity & Access Management}

Error: parse: parse spec: parse operations: paths: tmp4: post: operation "": parameters: parse parameter "Country Code": unsupported parameter type "body"
